      "message": "I need help on this from someone else.\n\nI haven\u0027t observed an actual case like data corruption caused by reboot.\n\nAdditionally I am not 100% sure what difference this makes.\nAs far as I read from the document, in theory, this is different from \"reboot --force\". However not yet sure if this is different from \"reboot\".\n\nAs far as I get from the document, the call chain is:\npowerd --\u003e powerd_setuid_helper --\u003e initctl emit --\u003e upstart reboot job --\u003e cascade of toher jobs in /etc/init --\u003e halt/reboot --force\n\nIn order to literally invoke powerd, we might need to make a DBus call to powerd.\n\nThis change is equivalent to \"initctl emit\" layer, but I am not sure the simple \"reboot\" is different. (it may also simply set the runlevel.)",
